---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const components=['Button','Field','Tabs','Select','Dialog','Popover','Date Picker'];
const frameworks=['React','Vue','Svelte','Solid'];
---
<Layout title="Architecture bake-off · Kumo">
<header><p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Candidates</a> / Bake-off</p><h1>Architecture evidence matrix</h1><p>Seven representative components × four frameworks × three candidates. Statuses describe checked-in evidence, not architectural preference.</p></header>
<aside><strong>No winner is declared.</strong> The candidates have materially different proof depth. Scores are counts by category—not a weighted ranking.</aside>
<section class="legend"><h2>Vocabulary</h2><p><b>passed</b>: required evidence exists. <b>partial</b>: some evidence exists, required gates remain not-run. <b>not-run</b>: no execution evidence. <b>blocked</b>: execution was attempted but could not proceed.</p></section>
<section><h2>Score categories</h2><div class="table"><table><thead><tr><th>Candidate</th><th>Passed targets</th><th>Partial targets</th><th>Passed gates</th><th>Not-run gates</th><th>Scope</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><th>Internal TypeScript control</th><td>28 control</td><td>0</td><td>Authority-backed</td><td>—</td><td>Existing full-emitter/browser authority, summarized as control</td></tr><tr><th><a href="/mitosis/">Mitosis</a></th><td>4</td><td>24</td><td>76</td><td>372</td><td>Button client build + Chromium only</td></tr><tr><th><a href="/shared-core/">Shared core</a></th><td>0</td><td>28</td><td>116 core/type/maintainability</td><td>220</td><td>Zero target-browser executions</td></tr></tbody></table></div></section>
<section><h2>84 target/candidate comparisons</h2><div class="table matrix"><table><thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>Framework</th><th>Internal TypeScript control</th><th>Mitosis</th><th>Shared core</th></tr></thead><tbody>{components.flatMap(component=>frameworks.map(framework=><tr><th>{component}</th><td>{framework}</td><td class="pass">passed (control)</td><td class={component==='Button'?'pass':'partial'}>{component==='Button'?'passed':'partial'}</td><td class="partial">partial</td></tr>))}</tbody></table></div></section>
<section class="notes"><h2>Interpretation limits</h2><ul><li>The internal TypeScript baseline is an existing authority-backed control, not a new run in this pilot.</li><li>Mitosis generated 28 sources, but only Button’s four framework targets have build and browser interaction proof.</li><li>Shared-core’s 116 passed gates cover reducers/contracts, types, and maintainability. They never imply a browser pass.</li><li>No candidate should receive credit for a not-run gate, and no “partial” cell is equivalent to passed.</li></ul></section>
<section class="notes"><h2>Select pilot update</h2><p><a href="/select-pilot/">The focused Select comparison</a> distinguishes 8/8 contract vectors, structural builds, four actual Solid browser failures, and blocked React/Vue/Svelte gates. It also records consumer DX at 3 passed / 22 blocked / 6 not-run. No winner is declared.</p></section>
</Layout>
<style>header{max-width:880px;padding:32px 0 12px}h1{font-size:clamp(38px,5vw,58px);margin:8px 0;letter-spacing:-.04em}header>p:last-child,.legend p,.notes{color:#475569;line-height:1.65}.eyebrow{font-size:12px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em}aside{margin:24px 0;padding:18px 20px;border-left:4px solid #d97706;background:#fffbeb;line-height:1.6}section{margin:38px 0}.table{overflow:auto;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:9px}table{width:100%;min-width:820px;border-collapse:collapse;background:white}th,td{padding:11px;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;text-align:left;vertical-align:top;font-size:13px}.matrix tbody tr:nth-child(4n+1){border-top:2px solid #94a3b8}.pass{color:#166534}.partial{color:#92400e}.notes{max-width:850px}.notes li{margin:8px 0}</style>